We faced a similar problem in a project I worked on.  We solved it by using
a modification of JUnit which featured non-fatal asserts (found here:
http://www.gnufoo.org/junit/index.html#failures).  We then implemented a
property file-driven testing architecture which allowed one &quot;test&quot; method to
run a variety of different test scenarios that we had placed in these
property files.  There was one library property file that contained a list
of the test property files to be run.  Then we could add/remove scenarios as
we wished.  I&#39;m sure there is a better way, but this worked for us.

Josh

